---
description: BRAIN Framework routing rule
globs:
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/fm/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/fm/**/*.md"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/pm/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/pm/**/*.md"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/kc/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/kc/**/*.md"
alwaysApply: true
---

This rule determines which schema applies to each page type.

Routing logic:

- If the file path contains `/fm/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/functional-mechanism-schema.md`

- If the file path contains `/pm/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/primary-mechanism-schema.md`

- If the file path contains `/kc/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/key-constraint-schema.md`

Conflict prevention:

- Must not mix FM, PM, and KC schemas in the same file
- Must not infer page type from content; use file path only

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
